Poll: Kubernetes or Bare Metal
text: I'm curious to know how many people here are advocates for Kubernetes or would prefer bare metal. I've seen some signs of a move to simpler architectures for self hosted software, often just running a bare metal server or a VM. I was a huge advocate for cluster based cloud platforms early on in the life of Kubernetes just because of exposure to Google and this love of scale, but now as an individual I'm leaning back in the direction of something simpler with less moving parts. Interested to hear what others think.
